text.section:
A certificate of notice may describe:
An action by the corporation, its board of directors, or its stockholders;
The occurrence of or change to facts ascertainable outside of the charter, as defined in § 2-105(b) of this article;
The expiration of the period of existence of the corporation in accordance with § 3-519 of this article; or
Any other information that the corporation determines should be disclosed.
